# Component Design

- Keep components under 200 lines when practical.
- Extract reusable UI into shared components.
- Prefer controlled components for forms.
- Separate presentation from business logic.
- Use meaningful prop names.
- Avoid prop drilling when context is more appropriate.

# Styling

- Follow the existing design system.
- Maintain consistent spacing and typography.
- Use responsive layouts.
- Ensure dark mode compatibility if supported.
- Avoid inline styles unless dynamic.

# Forms

Every form must:

- Validate client-side and server-side
- Display helpful error messages
- Disable submit while processing
- Prevent duplicate submissions
- Show loading indicators
- Preserve entered values on validation errors

# UX

Every feature should include loading, empty, error, and success states, plus a clear call-to-action.

# Error Handling (UI)

Never fail silently. Catch expected errors, show user-friendly messages, and provide recovery options.
